Here's the minimal vim config that reproduces the error on my machine:
```
call plug#begin('~/.nvim/plugged')
Plug 'nvim-treesitter/nvim-treesitter', {'do': ':TSUpdate'}
call plug#end()

lua <<EOF
  require'nvim-treesitter.configs'.setup {
    highlight = {
      enable = true,
    },
  }
EOF
```

Some things that were also critical:
1. I had to `set ft=markdown` to get the bug to trigger. (presumably because this turns on treesitter highlighting)
2. Had to move down a few lines in my markdown file, then pressing `o  >  esc`; or `o  >  esc  >  u`; a few times would usually trigger the bug.

Going to see if I can create a more minimal markdown file to share.

`TSConfigInfo`:
```
{
  auto_install = false,
  ensure_installed = {},
  ignore_install = {},
  modules = {
    highlight = {
      additional_vim_regex_highlighting = false,
      custom_captures = {},
      disable = {},
      enable = true,
      loaded = true,
      module_path = "nvim-treesitter.highlight"
    },
    incremental_selection = {
      disable = {},
      enable = false,
      keymaps = {
        init_selection = "gnn",
        node_decremental = "grm",
        node_incremental = "grn",
        scope_incremental = "grc"
      },
      module_path = "nvim-treesitter.incremental_selection"
    },
    indent = {
      disable = {},
      enable = false,
      module_path = "nvim-treesitter.indent"
    }
  },
  sync_install = false
}
```

Took another look at the above code. If I'm reading it right:

When roundup_32 was originally added it was used for allocated extra space: ([commit](https://github.com/MDeiml/tree-sitter-markdown/blob/27345783ee40874c0183064cc751467c6846e8b6/tree-sitter-markdown/src/scanner.c#L276))
```
+          s->open_blocks.capacity = roundup_32(blocks_count);
+          s->open_blocks.items = malloc(sizeof(Block) * s->open_blocks.capacity);
+          memcpy(s->open_blocks.items, &buffer[i], blocks_size);
```

But in the current version it's rounding up capacity but never allocates based on that capacity: https://github.com/MDeiml/tree-sitter-markdown/blob/aaf76797aa8ecd9a5e78e0ec3681941de6c945ee/tree-sitter-markdown/src/scanner.c#L279

The allocation happens later push_block, so could it be possible that capacity is higher than it should be? I think just removing the `roundup_32` would fix it?
